{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"Round-4 — incorporated reviewer feedback (maintainability + reliability + rationale capture):\n\n- **Sub-decomposed the heavy stories.** S2 → tasks S2a (89f9 selection+rebase-routing+stdlib Gerrit helper), S2b (a9e3 wipChain+TOCTOU+hand-back), S2c (1ccf fresh-Verified-per-member+atomic-submit). S5 → tasks S5a (08e1 container+compose+flock+volume), S5b (ea61 credentials+All-Projects capability), S5c (9a6f observability+status-endpoint), S5d (38be liveness+heartbeat+emergency-stop+drain+crash-recovery). Story-level AC trimmed to \"what/why\" with pointers to children; each task is now loadable whole (module-size ethos). S4 left intact (coherent, already signed).\n- **Reliability fallback (accepted):** S5d adds a CONCRETE crash-safe recovery record (`recovery.json` snapshot in the state volume) reconciled against live Gerrit + S3 markers on restart (no double-submit, no stranded stack) + an explicit crash-recovery/idempotency TEST that kills the bot at each phase. This also clears S5's round-3 BLOCK on the underspecified SIGTERM recovery contract.\n- **High-visibility failures (operability):** S5c makes hangs/errors/stuck-states loud — `autolander_errors` from three feeders (AUTOLANDER_ERROR marker on ANY unhandled error + hand-back, docker-inspect unhealthy, lander_down), a named `autolander_time_to_land_seconds` metric (clears the unnamed-metric BLOCK), and a stuck-state time-in-phase alarm.\n- **Provisioning fork resolved:** All-Projects capability grant committed to a concrete new file `infra/gerrit/setup-all-projects.sh` (clears S5's fork BLOCKs); `loop.py` now appears in child Files (clears the COH BLOCK).\n- **Rationale captured in ADR-0042:** full decision record drafted now (attached to S6) — the 8 key decisions + prior-art grounding + R5 invariant + separation-of-concerns + reliability tradeoff + the DEFERRAL TRIGGERS for the future idea-epics (1701 provider-seam, c3a9 bounded-speculation batching, HA). S6's AC updated to require landing exactly that.\n\nRound-3 state before this: epic/S2/S4 PASS+signed; S5 blocked (7). Re-running review on the trimmed S2/S5, S6, and the 7 new tasks."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783825485816136001,"uuid":"4268d964-00a6-4c64-8d59-4807f5c8f1b5"}